====================================================================== 
1) Affected Software 

* Lotus Notes 7.0.2 and 7.0.3

NOTE: Other versions may also be affected.

====================================================================== 
2) Severity 

Rating: Highly critical
Impact: System compromise
Where:  Remote

====================================================================== 
3) Vendor's Description of Software 

"Security-rich software that enables businesses to communicate,
collaborate and increase productivity."

Product Link:
http://www-306.ibm.com/software/lotus/ 

====================================================================== 
4) Description of Vulnerability

Secunia Research has discovered a vulnerability in Lotus Notes,
which can be exploited by malicious people to compromise a user's
system.

A boundary error within kvdocve.dll when processing overly long paths
can be exploited to cause a buffer overflow via e.g. an overly long
link inside the "src" attribute of an <IMG> tag in an HTML
document.

====================================================================== 
5) Solution 

Apply patch available from the vendor.

====================================================================== 
6) Time Table 

07/01/2008 - Vendor notified.
07/01/2008 - Vendor response.
08/04/2008 - Public disclosure.

====================================================================== 
7) Credits 

Discovered by Secunia Research.

====================================================================== 
8) References

The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) project has assigned 
CVE-2008-1101 for the vulnerability

